title: Grateful Dead Live at Madison Square Garden on 1991-09-13
lineage: 16 bit 48kHz DAT Master > TASCAM DA-20 (SPDIF out) ->  LynxTWO-B Audio Reference Interface (SPDIF in) ->  Wavelab 6.0 by Todd Evans (todd@bluedakota.com) October 30, 2008   Editing and Mastering: Jamie Waddell (shnflac@gmail.com) on the GEMS Edit Station. description:
Set 1

Touch Of Grey 
Wang Dang Doodle 
Peggy-O 
Big River ->
Cumberland Blues 
Althea 
When I Paint My Masterpiece 
Bird Song 

Set 2

Victim Or The Crime 
Scarlet Begonias ->
Fire On The Mountain ->
Drums ->
Space ->
The Other One ->
Stella Blue ->
Throwing Stones ->
Not Fade Away 

Encore
Knockin' On Heaven's Door

reviews.review_text: sleeper night  Mr. Brennecke and Mr. Young bring us right into the middle of the party and if you're not fixated on the Dead showing up in NYC and making a big statement at each, or at any of these nine shows, you're left to dig a pretty enjoyable Dead show.  Nothing too fancy, nothing that will end up on the yearly highlight reel but you can't quarrel with the expansive Scarlet>Fire into drums except to wish they nurtured that transition a little bit more instead of just unplugging the guitars and leaving the stage.  Low key is the tone of the night; even the Other One has fewer peaks and valleys.  Maybe tomorrow night they'll be more awake.

Great shiow The night Jerry died I was to head down the shore, I stopped in to see a bud and we played this show as a memorial.  Great up temp Peggy O, Never before Big River into Cumberland.   Great Masterpiece when Bobby really shown.    Monster VIctim> Foolish.   Mystified why this is seen as a low energy show.  No Bruce which opens up more room for Bob and Jerry ,
